# Image Converter - JPG/PNG to Transparent PNG

A simple desktop application built with **PySide6** and **rembg** that allows users to convert images (JPG, PNG, etc.) into **transparent PNGs**. The app supports both **local files** and **image URLs**.

---

## Features

- Select a local image file from your computer.
- Download an image directly from a URL.
- Convert the selected image to PNG with a transparent background.
- Simple, user-friendly graphical interface (GUI) with PySide6.
- Supports batch folder processing (optional via code).

---

## Requirements

- Python 3.9+
- [PySide6](https://pypi.org/project/PySide6/)
- [rembg](https://pypi.org/project/rembg/)
- [requests](https://pypi.org/project/requests/)

Install dependencies via pip:

```bash
pip install PySide6 rembg requests
```

For all requirements installation for rembg go to [rembg](https://pypi.org/project/rembg/)

## Usage
Clone or download the repository.

Run the application:
```bash
python main.py
```

Use the GUI to:

- Select a local file, or

- Enter an image URL and download it

- Click "Transformer l'image" to convert the image to a transparent PNG.

The converted PNG will be saved in the same folder as the input file.

## Exe file
To make exe file you can use pyinstaller
```bash
pyinstaller --onefile --windowed main.py
```